n > N
S_n = \sum_{k=0}^n c_k
 \left| \left( \frac 1n \sum_{k=1}^n S_k \right) - S \right| = \frac 1n \left| \sum_{k=1}^n (S_k - S) \right| \le \frac 1n \sum_{k=1}^n |S_k - S| = \frac {\sum_{k=1}^{\ell} |S_k - S|}{n} + \frac {\sum_{k=\ell+1}^n |S_k - S|}{n} 
 \frac{\sum_{k=1}^{\ell} |S_k - S|}{n} < \varepsilon / 2. 
 \frac {\sum_{k=1}^{\ell} |S_k - S|}{n} + \frac {\sum_{k=\ell+1}^n |S_k - S|}{n} \le \frac {\sum_{k=1}^{\ell} |S_k - S|}{n} + \frac{(n-\ell) (\varepsilon/2)}n  \le \varepsilon. 
